  "text": "We have listed the experiential setup in Tables I and II . We consider 200 edge devices which are distributed over an area of 1000 m × 1000 m and one macro base station (MBS) co-located to a MEC server. The MEC server located in the MBS, whose computation capability is 100 GHz and the computation capability of edge device is 0.7 GHz. Each base station has 50 orthogonal wireless channels for the computational service offloading from edge devices to edge servers. Here, the cellular backhaul delay coefficient is considered to be 0.0001 sec/kB [CITATION_1] . The total time duration to offload the computation services of mobile edge devices are randomly distributed between 5 and 10 ms. The corresponding computation file size of each computational service varies within the range 300-800 kB. The delay requirements of edge devices is considered to be within the range 0.5-1 s.",
